newsitem.title: TUNISIA: Tunisian treasury raises 53 mln dinars at auction.
newsitem.headline: Tunisian treasury raises 53 mln dinars at auction.

text.p: The Tunisian Treasury on Tuesday said it sold 53 million dinars of three-year notes at its weekly auction on November 26, repaying maturing paper totalling 40.9 million dinars.
The three-year notes payable in equal annual tranches were at a 8.0625 coupon rate, unchanged from their level last week.
Banks bid for 125 million dinars of three-, and five-year notes at between 8.0625 and 8.5 percent. ($=0.98 dinar)
